notes: Need to see abundance map, but overall it appears to show movement between C Chile to N Chile and Bolivia in winter, and captures small pocket populations as well as overall use of Andes.

Doesn't pick up the breeding population in the 'stans, and overextrapolates into the Indus Valley in Pakistan as with many Indian species modeled so far. In core Indian range seems to be well-detailed to an untrained eye.

Seems to overall be quite goodâ€”some very low abundance wintering populations in E Med are not picked up, but the core populations are. Migration back east into the Med Sea seems good, and wintering abundance in NW Africa seems spot on.

Seems to be pretty great at capturing coastal distribution of the species throughout the annual cycle, including vacating the breeding islands in Aug-Sep, and returning slowly between Sep and March. Hard to code specific seasons; not sure if it'll make sense as currently coded. Need to see abundance map.
Expected global species problems (no Russia; overextrap in W Africa and Middle East; blinkiness in many regions; no coverage in much of Africa), but otherwise seems pretty good!
Breeding might be a total failure, but want to see what a map would look likeâ€”it might work from the few weeks. Otherwise, non-breeding looks pretty good, and migration seems workable.

Seems to overall capture range in general, but overextrapolate heavily given few positive obs, especially through southern AR and parts of central CL. Curious to evaluate from seasonal map; may need to change based on that.
